  <!--
    Google Maps API key — read by the native Google Maps Android SDK at startup.
    react-native-maps requires this resource to be present.

    HOW TO SET:
      Replace PASTE_YOUR_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_HERE with your AIza... key.
      Get your key at: https://console.cloud.google.com
        → APIs & Services → Credentials → Create API Key
        → Enable "Maps SDK for Android"
        → Restrict the key to com.seq.app (Android app restriction)

    The same key used for the JavaScript API (eas.json GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY)
    works here if you leave the API restrictions set to "Maps SDK for Android"
    AND "Maps JavaScript API". Or use the same unrestricted key for simplicity
    and add restrictions later.

    DO NOT commit a real key to git — use a git-ignored local override or
    inject via CI. For EAS builds, use an EAS secret and a config plugin
    to write it here at build time, OR simply paste it once and keep this
    file out of public repositories.
  -->
  <string name="google_maps_api_key" translatable="false">PASTE_YOUR_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_HERE</string>
</resources>
